data.title: We recognized nine dedicated Knoxville Police Department officers who are moving into new leaderships roles during a promotional ceremony...
data.meta_description:
253 likes, 6 comments - knoxville_pd on October 19, 2023: "We recognized nine dedicated Knoxville Police Department officers who are moving into new leaderships roles during a promotional ceremony this afternoon at the Civic Coliseum Auditorium. 

Officers Dylan Bradley, Andrew Cloyd, Carl Kennedy, James Vesser and Preston Whillock were promoted to Sergeant. 

Sergeants Brian Dalton, Michael Geddings and Nate Skellenger were promoted to Lieutenant. 

Lieutenant Tammy DeBow was promoted to Captain, becoming the newest member of the departmentâ€™s Command Staff. 

Congratulations to all of these officers, and thank you for accepting the responsibility that comes with these new supervisory roles.".
